<br>
It's really not such a big issue to us financially which currency Iraq decides to trade its oil in.  If they pick euros, that can be good or bad for us, depending on the strength of the dollar.  People trading oil in euros has no impact on the desirability of the dollar for investments really.  The primary concern is inflation control and responsible fiscal policy.  So long as the US isn't going nuts printing money, which it doesn't, the dollar will remain the most stable and inflation resistant currency.  People just want to be sure the currency they put their money in will hold its value.<br>
<br>
The financial impacts of what currency Iraq trades its oil in are not anywhere near severe enough to justify a war.  They're actually quite minor.<br>
