People have a great tendancy to oversimplify causation.  We are there for quite a few different reasons that all came together in the minds of our leaders to move us to war.  I believe oil is an insignificant part of it.  However, it's certainly not just 1 reason that drove us to war.  It's liberation of the Iraqi people, punishment of Saddam for invading Kuwait, Saddam's continued defiance of the UN, his development of WMD's, his links to terrorist organizations, 9/11 and the general backlash that created, a more hawkish policy of the new administration that all came together to bring us to war.  Anyone that says &quot;We are in the middle east for one reason,and one reason only, ... &quot; is full of crap.  Take an advanced history course sometime, and every single historical event that you seek to explain will be explained with 20 different reasons as contributing factors.  Things are never so simple as to have 1 reason.<br>
